{
  "texts": [
    "In other words, these methods can determine whether the dissemination of disinformation aims to deceive and mislead the audience or not (Zhou and Zafarani 2020).",
    "In disinformation, a distinct writing style is often employed to attract and persuade a wide range of audiences, which differs from the writing style used in true information (Shu et al. 2017).",
    "Writing style can be determined by analyzing both textual and visual features.",
    "Therefore, style-based methods attempt to differentiate disinformation from true information by extracting and analyzing these features.",
    "The writing style can vary across different fields and languages and may also evolve over time (Zhou and Zafarani 2020)."
  ]
}